Terminalia (
Figs 3C, D
; 
4C, D
).

Tergite 9 slightly ovoid, with very dense patch of spines of equal length concentrated on apex. Gonostyli tapering, as long as apical tooth, with dense patch of apical setae. Aedeagal complex heavily sclerotised, conical, with rounded apex. Aedeagal apodemes long, straight, unbranched, directed medially.
